label: C/C++ Project  DB Internals

name: Write Your Own Virtual Machine (LC-3 VM)
description: Implement an LC-3 (or similar educational ISA) virtual machine in C. Build memory/register models, instruction decoding/dispatch, I/O traps, and a debugger harness to understand CPU design and VM execution semantics.
label: C/C++ Project  VM Internals

name: Learning KVM  Implement Your Own Kernel Module
description: Follow a KVM learning series to implement hypervisor features in C inside the Linux kernel. Learn how CPU virtualization is exposed and handled via KVM and how guest/host transitions work.

label: C/C++ Project  Compiler Design

label: C/C++ Project  LLVM IR

label: C/C++ Project  Template Magic

name: High-Performance Matrix Multiplication
description: Implement optimized matrix multiplication using loop unrolling, cache blocking, SIMD intrinsics, and multithreading. Benchmark against BLAS and analyze high-performance memory and CPU behavior.
label: C/C++ Project  HPC Skills

name: Space Invaders from Scratch
description: Create a complete Space Invaders clone in C++. Implement entity movement, bullets, collisions, enemy waves, scoring, and sound. Arrange your game loop, rendering, and entity system cleanly.

name: Tetris in C++ (Platform Independent)
description: Develop a Tetris clone in pure C++ implementing piece rotation, falling logic, collision detection, row clearing, scoring, and progressive speed increase. Focus on isolating game logic from rendering for portability.
label: C/C++ Project  Puzzle Game

name: Write a Linux Debugger
description: Implement a real Linux debugger using ptrace, capable of setting breakpoints, stepping, reading registers, loading symbols, and interpreting DWARF debug info. A very advanced low-level systems project.
label: C/C++ Project  Debugging Internals

name: Let's Code a TCP/IP Stack
description: Implement a minimal TCP/IP stack in C to learn networking from the ground up. Start at the data-link layer (Ethernet/ARP), move to IPv4 and ICMP, then implement TCP basics including the three-way handshake, socket-like API for user interaction, and TCP reliability features like retransmission. This project gives deep, hands-on understanding of packet formats, checksums, state machines, and how high-level sockets map to low-level packets.
label: Network Internals

name: Programming Concurrent Servers
description: Build a series of concurrent server implementations to learn concurrency models and I/O strategies. Start with a threaded server, then implement event-driven and async designs, study libuv for cross-platform async I/O, and analyze a real-world case (Redis) to understand production patterns. Finish by comparing callbacks, promises and async/await styles.
label: Concurrency Mastery

name: Build an Interpreter (Chapters 413 in Java)
description: Implement a full interpreter for a small programming language using Java (following Chapters 413 style). Start with a lexer and parser, build an AST, and implement a tree-walk evaluator. Add a REPL and file-execution mode, then extend with functions, closures, and a small standard library. Focus on strong error messages, memory-safe design using Java objects, and tests.
label: Java Project  Practical Java

name: Build a Simple HTTP Server with Java
description: Create a minimal HTTP server in Java from socket-level primitives up to handling GET/POST requests. Implement HTTP parsing, response generation, headers, basic routing, and static file serving. Optionally add threading or an event-driven loop for concurrency and add simple logging and configurable ports.
label: Java Project  Networking Basics

name: Build an Android Flashlight App (video)
description: Make a simple Android app that toggles the device flashlight using the camera/torch API. Focus on minimal UI, runtime permission handling, and lifecycle safety (release camera resources). This is a great beginner Android project demonstrating permissions, hardware access, and basic UI.
label: Java Project  Beginner Mobile

name: Build a Spring Boot App with User Authentication
description: Develop a Spring Boot web application that implements user registration, login, logout, and role-based access control. Use Spring Security for authentication/authorization, password hashing, and session management. Add a simple frontend (Thymeleaf or SPA) and secure REST endpoints for authenticated users.
label: Java Project  Web Authentication

name: Build a Library Management System in Java Swing
description: Create a desktop Library Management System using Java Swing for GUI: manage books, members, check-in/check-out, and simple search. Include persistence via an embedded database (H2 / SQLite) and support for printing/exporting reports. Emphasize clean UI, validation, and modular design separating UI and data layers.
